HEADWORD: Pimaric
<hw>Pi*mar"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>pi</ets>num <ets>mar</ets>itima, an old name for <spn>Pinum
Pinaster</spn>, a pine which yields galipot.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid found in galipot, and
isomeric with abietic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pimelic</ent>⟦br⟧
